description:
Lunacid is a first person dungeon crawler inspired by old FROMSOFT games like Shadow Tower and King’s Field.

Long ago a great beast arose from the sea and covered the earth in a poison fog. Now those deemed undesirable
are thrown into a great well, which has become a pit of chaos and disease. You awaken in a moonlit subterranean world,
having been thrown into the Great Well for crimes unknown. The only way out is to go further down and confront the
sleeping old one below. On the way there will be many creatures and secrets to discover.

1.0.0-pre1.description:
## Lunacid Randomizer v1.0.0 Pre-Release
This is absolutely not in any way compatible with anything before.

# New Features/Changes:
- Random equipment stats.
- Weapons are named respective of their new element.
- In-game UI settings.
  - You can change ports at the main menu.
  - Can change EXP, WEXP multipliers, Custom Colors, Custom Music, Normalized Drops in-game.
    - This means these settings are removed from the yaml.
- Custom Music, Saves are moved to the plugin folder, for cleanliness.
- Split ConnectionData and SlotData information into two different JSONS, just in case you absolutely need to change the jsons.
- Items now trickle in every one second so you can read them.
- Traps are now in a queue, and should trigger only if you're in a proper game state, and the previous effect is not applied.
- New Traps!
  - Rat Gang.  Spawns 5 rats and they sing to you.
  - Date with Death.  You are force teleported to a map where death will instantly kill you.  Get the hell out of there!
- Entering the fight with Sucsarius without Lucid Blade leaves you with no weapon and killable, instead of just killing you.
- New challenge/skip features.
  - Tricks and Glitches tend to put certain access into logic.
  - No logic setting, for people wanting to see what's possible or not.
- New location in Yosei Forest.  There was a rusted sword not accounted for.
- Split Vampiric Symbols.  Now you can get the symbols out of order if you want to.
- Custom game information has been pulled out of the main game and now lives in a folder the player can modify.
- Took out the poptracker pack embedded in the apworld, should now ask the user to supply theirs.

# Bugfixes
- Deathlink works now.

# Things to investigate.
- Save stability.  And if saving is not stable and people lose information, why.
- Item stability; the item receiving system has changed.  Do you get the previous item when you shouldn't, etc?
- Custom game support.  Does changing them work appropriately, do they show up appropriately, etc.
- Equipment stat locks/problems.  Can certain combinations have bad outcomes?
- Took out the poptracker pack.  How functional is all that?
- New logic changes means new logic problems.  Are there any problems?
1.0.0-pre1.title: Lunacid Randomizer v1.0.0 Pre-Release 1

1.0.0-pre5.description:
This is likely the final update for features.

New Features:
- Auto Hints: A new option in a bad spot in the menu, hooway.  If its on, when you use Light Reveal, check a shop, or use Bestial Communion after receiving Bestial Mastery, the location will be autohinted if its important.
- RingLink: By popular demand of one person and it was enough.  Silver is linked.  Mimics will beat your ass.  You will afford everything in two seconds.
- New Items:
  - Demi's Gift for a Stranger: if you get this, if another player in the multiworld has an open gift box, will give them a random gift.  Otherwise its the same as nothing.
  - Patchouli's Gift for a Stranger: the above, but a trap.

Changes:
- Code regarding item sending/receiving and traps in general may be improved.  I made them going away on a disconnect a bit cleaner.
- Make a catch so the seed of the slot is compared with the seed from SlotData when loading a save, and if they mismatch it won't let you load the save.
- Probably some other shit idk

1.0.0-pre6.description:
Could be final?  Could be lying?  Lmao?

New Features:
- Lore spots glow now.  Yippee.
- The two compasses the games use now point at the nearest active location in the game.
  - If the location is not instantiated in some way, it will not point to it.  Examples include
    - Does not point to monsters in dropsanity.  Will point to their drops.
    - Likely doesn't point to chests, because the item shows up upon opening.
    - The corner spot you hit with a ranged attack, the tree staring spot, have nothing to point to.
    - etc.
  - If no pickups exists in the scene it will have default behavior.
  - It does not consider logic.  It just points at the nearest thing. 

Bugfix:
- It was possible to start with a spell you couldn't cast due to weapon stat shuffling.  Starting spells now have a maximum cost of 10.
1.0.0-pre6.title: Lunacid Randomizer v1.0.0 Pre-Release 6

1.0.0-pre7.description:
The things I do to not refactor some other rando.

THIS IS NOT COMPATIBLE WITH ANYTHING UNDER THIS DO NOT EVEN ATTEMPT TO DO IT.

Changes:
- The save system no longer heavily relies on jsons, and instead the entire save structure of the game is modified to be split between the standard save and multiworld saves.  These saves have .MIDNIGHTMULTI as an extension, unlike normal .MIDNIGHT files.  This was done in some attempt to stop information loss and try to be more clean about saving information.
- Added a few hopeful mainstay log "tells" for bad behavior.  Should help with bug reporting in the future.

Bugfixes:
- Compass no longer spams errors.

Known Bug:
- When breaking and collecting breakable/grass locations the compass continues to point to them.

1.0.0-release.description:
## Lunacid Randomizer v1.0.0 Release
Lets just call this one the full release, and anything else is fun extra or whatever, eh?

# New Features/Changes:
- Random equipment stats.
- Weapons are named respective of their new element.
- In-game UI settings.
  - You can change ports at the main menu.
  - Can change EXP, WEXP multipliers, Custom Colors, Custom Music, Normalized Drops in-game.
    - This means these settings are removed from the yaml.
- Custom Music, Saves are moved to the plugin folder, for cleanliness.
- Game and Item custom information is made into open JSONS.  Can be edited later.
- All old save data is now tied to the actual game's save system.  Uses a .MIDNIGHTMULTI format.
  - This also applies to settings, so initial launch requires setup.
- Items now trickle in every one second so you can read them.
- Traps are now in a queue, and should trigger only if you're in a proper game state, and the previous effect is not applied.
- New Traps!
  - Rat Gang.  Spawns 5 rats and they sing to you.  Rats, we're rats, we're the rats~
  - Date with Death.  You are force teleported to a map where death might be.  Get the hell out of there!  Default 0 weight since its mean.
- Entering the fight with Sucsarius without Lucid Blade leaves you with no weapon and killable, instead of just killing you.
- New challenge/skip features.
  - Tricks and Glitches tend to put certain access into logic.
  - No logic setting, for people wanting to see what's possible or not.
- New location in Yosei Forest.  There was a rusted sword not accounted for.
- Split Vampiric Symbols.  Now you can get the symbols out of order if you want to.
- Ringlink: Your silver is tied to the ringlink system.  Mimics smile in anticipation.
- New gifting items!  Getting these sends a gift to another player instead, how nice!
  - Demi's is a gift, Patchouli's is a trap.
  - If no players receive gifts, its the same as a "nothing" item.
  - Default to 0 weight.
- Compasses now point to the nearest check in the current scene. 

# Bugfixes
- Deathlink works now.  Perish.
1.0.0-release.title: Lunacid Randomizer v1.0.0 Release
